        <details class=''>
          <summary>Is Wayki going to get my child/younger sibling to brush their teeth?</summary>
            <p>You bet! We've already done tests with this (not extensive) and after several days the habit sets in. The beauty of Wayki is that it creates good habits without any thought required, for chores that have historically required a little self motivation.<br>
The secret to getting anyone to do anything that isn't fun is to help them (1) understand the benefit, then (2) remove as much friction as possible. That's our philosophy anyway!<br>
Some other good timeless advice <a href="http://www.parentdish.com/2010/10/04/how-can-i-get-my-son-to-brush-his-teeth/" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>

